# Test Analysis: ui_element.h.spec.md
# Source: test_suite_ui_ui_element.c.report

## Failure 1
File: tests/core/source/ui/test_suite_ui_ui_element.c:255
Assertion: get_next__ui_element(&a) == NULL

### Symptom
`get_next__ui_element` returns a non-null pointer when null is expected.

### Root Cause
In `initialize_ui_element`, the spec (§4.4.8) states that
`link_ui_element_to__this_ui_element` with a self-link sets `p_next` to null.
The test likely calls `link_ui_element_to__this_ui_element(&a, &a)` and
expects `a.p_next == NULL`. The inline function must check for self-link and
assign null instead of the self-pointer.

### Spec Reference
§4.4.8: "Self-link sets `p_next` to null."

---

## Failure 2
File: tests/core/source/ui/test_suite_ui_ui_element.c:290
Assertion: is_ui_element__using_sprite(&ui_element) is not true

### Symptom
After calling `set_ui_element__sprite`, `is_ui_element__using_sprite` returns
false.

### Root Cause
`set_ui_element__sprite` is declared in the spec (§4.4.5) but its
implementation is not present in `ui_element.c`. The function must call
`set_ui_element_as__using_sprite` to set the
`UI_FLAGS__BIT_IS_USING__SPRITE_OR_UI_TILE_SPAN` flag. Without this, the flag
remains unset and `is_ui_element__using_sprite` returns false.

### Spec Reference
§4.4.5: "`set_ui_element__sprite`: Associates a sprite and sets sprite
rendering mode."
§4.4.11: "`set_ui_element_as__using_sprite`: Sets
`IS_USING__SPRITE_OR_UI_TILE_SPAN`."

---

## Failure 3
File: tests/core/source/ui/test_suite_ui_ui_element.c:420
Assertion: does_ui_element_have__transformed_handler(&ui_element) is not false

### Symptom
After a fresh `initialize_ui_element`, `does_ui_element_have__transformed_handler`
returns true when the test expects false.

### Root Cause
`initialize_ui_element` unconditionally calls
`set_ui_element__transformed_handler(p_ui_element,
m_ui_element__transformed_handler__default)`, installing a non-null handler.
The spec (§4.4.1) states "All handlers set to null" during base
initialization. The default transformed handler should NOT be installed during
`initialize_ui_element`; it should be left null.

### Spec Reference
§4.4.1: "`initialize_ui_element`: All handlers set to null."

---

## Failure 4
File: tests/core/source/ui/test_suite_ui_ui_element.c:434
Assertion: does_ui_element_have__dispose_handler(&ui_element) is not false

### Symptom
After a fresh `initialize_ui_element`, `does_ui_element_have__dispose_handler`
returns true when the test expects false.

### Root Cause
`initialize_ui_element` unconditionally calls
`set_ui_element__dispose_handler(p_ui_element,
m_ui_element__dispose_handler__default)`, installing a non-null handler. The
spec (§4.4.1) states "All handlers set to null" during base initialization.
The default dispose handler should NOT be installed during
`initialize_ui_element`; it should be left null.

### Spec Reference
§4.4.1: "`initialize_ui_element`: All handlers set to null."

---

